title: Grateful Dead Live at Des Moines State Fair Grandstand on 1974-06-16
description:
Set 1

Bertha, Mexicali Blues, Row Jimmy, Beat It On Down The Line, Scarlet Begonias, Black Throated Wind, Sugaree, El Paso, It Must Have Been The Roses, Jack Straw, China Cat Sunflower> I Know You Rider, Around & Around

Set 2

U.S. Blues, The Race is On, Eyes Of The World-> Big River, Playin' In The Band, Tennessee Jed, Me & My Uncle, Deal, Greatest Story Ever Told, Ship Of Fools

Set 3

Truckin'-> Nobody's Fault But Mine-> Wharf Rat-> Goin' Down The Road Feelin' Bad, E: Casey Jones

Setlist order not 100% certain. The list here is given in the order of a ~1999-circulated SBD.

reviews.review_text:
KEITH This is a phenomenal audience recording of one of my all-time favorite shows. 

Yes, it's too bad that some stuff gets cut but ... for cripesakes the performance is really top notch.  Everybody's on top of their game here, and Keith especially is just unleashing wave after wave of lysergic from his keyboard (first coupla songs he's on the piano but then he switches to the rhodes for Row Jimmy, then back and forth "as needed").  This recording captures that and also Bill's soul-shattering cymbal work amazingly well.

Bask in the glory!

* It aint no saxaphone -- that's Keith.
